# Component Organization

## Extract Reusable Components

When a component could be reused elsewhere, create it in a separate file:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Reusable button defined inline
function Dashboard() {
  const IconButton = ({ icon, onClick }) => (
    <button onClick={onClick}>{icon}</button>
  );
  
  return <IconButton icon="+" onClick={handleAdd} />;
}

// ✅ GOOD - Reusable component in its own file
// components/IconButton.tsx
export function IconButton({ icon, onClick }) {
  return <button onClick={onClick}>{icon}</button>;
}
```

## Split Visual Sections

Break down pages into logical visual section components:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Everything in one component
function ProfilePage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <div>{/* 50 lines of header markup */}</div>
      <div>{/* 80 lines of stats markup */}</div>
      <div>{/* 60 lines of activity feed markup */}</div>
    </div>
  );
}

// ✅ GOOD - Visual sections as separate components
function ProfilePage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <ProfileHeader user={user} />
      <ProfileStats stats={stats} />
      <ActivityFeed activities={activities} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Guidelines

- Create new files in a `components/` directory or colocated with the feature
- Each component file should export a single primary component
- Name files after the component they export (e.g., `ProfileHeader.tsx`)
